name: Gov. Asa Hutchinson
tweet: It'll take a few days to know whether the increase in hospitalizations is the result of buildup after the long Christmas weekend. Regardless, the high number of cases continues to strain our health care system. Regretfully, we have an additional 55 deaths.  https://t.co/M8osjzmwnc  https://t.co/3w3jhCKqeM

name: Gov. Asa Hutchinson
tweet: It is great news for Arkansans that the latest COVID-19 Relief bill has been signed by @realDonaldTrump. This will help our small businesses, individuals, schools and the state with vaccine distribution.

name: Gov. Asa Hutchinson
tweet: Yesterday was a much lower number of new cases, partly because of lower testing. Of the 41 deaths, 25 are delayed reporting from November. Regardless, this is a loss for all of us. Please continue to follow public health guidelines and recommendations.  Full report:  https://t.co/49PNCwhgGw

name: Gov. Asa Hutchinson
tweet: Yesterday we saw much lower case numbers across the state. This was expected, but the real test will be over the next two weeks. For all who had a more low key Christmas, thank you. Let’s all be careful over the weekend.  Full report:  https://t.co/MHz3nMH1ux

name: Gov. Asa Hutchinson
tweet: In this season of giving, consider helping your neighbor. The number of those with food insecurity has increased this year, and we can help. Donate to one of your local foodbanks today to help your fellow Arkansans.  https://t.co/vuNr4GSSzo

name: Gov. Asa Hutchinson
tweet: Here is today’s report. We have had a decline in hospitalizations, and the new cases are lower but remain over 2,000. We have a lot to do as a state and nation in the closing days of 2020 to turn the tide on the surging virus. It will take all of us.  Full report:  https://t.co/K06BYbjepu

name: Gov. Asa Hutchinson
tweet: There are 3,204 new COVID-19 cases in Arkansas. There are two keys to victory over the virus. Vaccines and vigilance. We must be vigilant even during this special season of the year. Vaccines are coming, but we all must be careful to keep our loved ones safe.    Full report:  https://t.co/juhzDXgWND
